What insurance is suitable for me?
Car insurance to protect drivers in the event of an accident. represents a significant expense that depends on various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of the driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the appropriate car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured person.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract stipulating that the insurance undertaking will receive an agreed insured amount of a certain amount for taking charge of the payment of damages in the event of an insured event.
Premiums are the price of insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of the driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the greater the likelihood of an accident, the higher the premium rate.
For this reason, both the over-25s and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of inspections, insurance companies concluded that persons living in marriage have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of journeys and thus the likelihood that it will have an accident.
Increasing the frequency of rides increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the price of premiums.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the insurance that best corresponds to his profile of the insured person.
Here we will show the most important variables for choosing one type of insurance, which, in addition to complying with the type of insured person, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of 25 face various disadvantages, such as little driving experience and short driving licences when they want to negotiate premiums at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are also cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks at a discount of premiums in order to obtain insurance coverage for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would assume the client's participation in the payment of the insured event.
"The part of the insurance claims provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the price of the premium, which will be all the higher the lower the deductible," explains Luis Noguera, Chief Executive of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other road users by insuring the client against damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
recommendation.
If you're under the age of 25, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to lower premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
Malus, on the other hand, is an increase in that base rate.
"The bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus," explains Noguera.
After crossing the 25-year limit, drivers have it easier when they go to take out insurance, as the client's risk index decreases, thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to take out insurance against all risks at a discount.
"Young people usually cannot take advantage of pre-earned experience when a crash occurs, nor can they drive," assures the director of a European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when the "fear of the newcomer" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to take out insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies to be the clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a discount of the premium (which could amount to 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other participants, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their management is calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford luxury to get the highest discount", says Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are advised to take out insurance against all risks at a discounted premium (which amounts to EUR 150) or insurance extended to other participants if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects drivers in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would suit us best in view of our personal situation.
