"She was my shield.
She'd protect me."
Mr. McCarthy said that Ms. Arroyo was the wife of Jimmy Arroyo, a former New York City police officer who works for the Alcoholic Beverage Control Commission, and that she leaves behind two sons, ages 14 and 11, and a stepdaughter.
Eileen Walsh, a spokeswoman for Union County District Attorney Theodore J. Romankow, said detectives are trying to determine if Ms. Arroyo died as a result of unlicensed surgery.
"It's one of the options," Ms. Walsh said.
"The investigation is still ongoing."
Authorities said they arrived at the house about 3 p.m. on March 21.
They found Miss Arroyo on the sofa.
She was pronounced dead at the scene.
More than a week later, authorities still said little about their investigation or the owner of the house, believed to be Flor Margarita Castro.
